reviews.text: This place is awesome! Great food and service. Really nice place. Met the owners and they were very nice and took time to stop and talk. The fried avocado is our personal favorite. The food and creative drinks are delicious. This was our 2nd time out of many more to come.

I felt immediately welcomed upon entering this restaurant tonight with my girlfriends. I needed to write a review immediately. We met our server/bartender who greeted us without hesitation although it was close to closing (without us knowing). He was clearly busy with three other tables/also tending the bar/closing duties- but I never felt rushed in his presence. There was not a wait, and it was if we have been regulars for years- which now I will be. The food was delicious and the drinks were truly superb. I can't wait to bring my family back here!

-Emma

My friends and I had an incredible experience here. Mateo was our bartender and server, he was charming, funny and really took the time to make sure we were well taken care of and having a great time. The food was unbelievably delicious. I cannot wait to come back, such great vibes!

Fantastic food and great server who was quick and attentive!!  Lots of variety for taco choices.  Carne Asada was great, pulled pork fantastic, the chicken one was a little dry.  We tried several appetizers as well, our fav was the queso and chips, the queso is PERFECTION

We stopped here on a whim for lunch because we were in the area. The staff were great - especially the bartender. He told us the story of how they got started and it felt like we had known him for years already! Such an easygoing, friendly atmosphere. The decor is absolutely stunning, I kept thinking that it was plucked straight out of Malibu or Miami. The carne asada tacos are probably the best tacos I have ever had in my life. I was taken aback by the authenticity and flavor of everything we tried. A suggestion - try the smash burger, and ask for the cucumber jalapeno sauce. We bought and took some home with us!

The food? Incredible. Every dish bursts with flavor, clearly made with love and attention to detail. The drinks are just as impressive‚Äîcreative, well-balanced, and delicious. You can tell the team here cares deeply about what they‚Äôre serving.

detailedReviews.author: Rocko
detailedReviews.text: I would leave half A star if I could.  The place initially looked cool when we first walked in.  But that feeling immediately changed with the proximity of the seating in the center, on the tiny tables.   On top of that, the music was pretty loud, both from the radio and then the live performance of a Billy Joel band at a Mexican taco joint? The food was seasoned well, but everything (literally everything) was served cold.  The fresh chips and salsa? Cold and somewhat stale.  The quesadilla I ordered half beef and half chicken? Good but cold.   The rice bowls.  All with cold meat and rice.    Then the prices! Incredibly expensive for the poor food quality.  Also also, why does it seem to be a Mexican restaurant with no body of any Latino ethnicity in sight? Everybody that came in was the whitest gentric family I've ever seen.  And this place has 5 star glaring ratings? Crazy.  Never going back.  El ranchito remains supreme.   Get good.

detailedReviews.author: Chris Polus
detailedReviews.text: Excellent food. The blend of protein and other ingredients are perfect. They even offer up extra sauces now to add to the flair. Portions are good for the prices. Just wish the tacos came with more then just the tacos. Maybe a side of rice and refried beans. Oh yeah, the drinks. I have tried almost all of them, worth the buy amd try. Staff has been very outgoing and courteous. They know how to treat you to bring you back.

detailedReviews.author: Mikhail
detailedReviews.text: We were nervous about this place because the decor gives modern "gentrified" mexican as you can see in the pictures. However our order came and wow. The flavors and spices are so nicely done. The owners are a married couple, the wife being mexican, and they have used passed down family secret recipes to create authentic marinades that taste incredible. Special props to the chef. Definitely coming back for DJ trivia nights on Tuesday's

detailedReviews.author: Lenny Johnson
detailedReviews.text: We went there for latin dance. While there, we ordered some tacos. They were good and reasonable. The drinks are average on price.

detailedReviews.author: Douglas Crandall
detailedReviews.text: The atmosphere is very inviting with comfortable seating and pleasing decor. You seat yourself and are recognized with a warm welcome. The menu tells you this is authentic Mexican cuisine and we were not disappointed with our meals. Our server was very helpful in helping us decide what to order. I went for their 3 taco üåÆ meal and my wife ordered a quesadilla meal. What a nice surprise to enjoy authentic Mexican cooking.- took us back to our time Mexico!

detailedReviews.author: Janet King

detailedReviews.author: Christa Lombardo
detailedReviews.text: Owner is super friendly. Restaurant is very clean. Food is wonderful.

detailedReviews.author: Lucinda Diaz
detailedReviews.text: Taquito Lindo is such a cute little restaurant, I love the way they have it decorated. The tacos, burritos and quesadillas are very tasty, and their guacamole‚Ä¶ they knock it out of the park.. FRESH & DELICIOUS everytime!!

detailedReviews.author: Dawn Macqueen
detailedReviews.text: We found our new favorite family restaurant! The place is HUGE, service was amazing! Lyon was our server and he was nothing less than personable, knowledgeable about the menu, and attentive. This was our first time here and even our hard to please toddler was impressed! The taco trio is a must try for a first timer. You can choose your protein (I did chicken, steak, and pork), and they come with different toppings. The pickled veggies on each taco added so much flavor to the proteins. My husband got a pork, bean, and veggies rice bowl (Barria??), which was amazing! It‚Äôs only made on Wednesday so 10/10 recommend. Of course we ordered chips and queso as an appetizer and requested more chip because they weren‚Äôt greasy or topped with oil. The queso was great. The kids menu .. the cheese quesadilla was HUGE hit with our little one. She doesn‚Äôt eat much when we go out to eat, and she ate 3/4 of the quesadilla. And let‚Äôs talk about the churros‚Ä¶ oh my taste buds! Sooooo yummy. All this to say the food, price, service, and atmosphere exceeded any and all expectations!

detailedReviews.text: Great food every time!
